  "text": "It can be found from Figure 6 that C11 is five-times larger than C31, as long as the xΣ is greater than 0.65 and α1 is less than 0.3. Meanwhile, K2/K6 is mostly positive and in the range of 0.3~3 [CITATION_1] ; thus, β1 is in the range of 1~2.5, indicating that G1(s) is a phase lead element with the maximum leading phase around 30 degrees. Therefore, ΔPe2 can be decomposed into two components, as shown in Figure 7a : Component 1 is in phase with ΔPSMES, and Component 2 leads ΔPSMES by 90°. If ΔPSMES is in phase with Δω, Component 1 will provide the damping torque, while Component 2 will act as a negative synchronous torque.",
